metadata.name: i thought i’d used up all the colours
metadata.description:
i took all the colours out and spread them around. they took on lives of their own, piled up on each other, clumped, oozed, smeared. i wormed my way between them, squeezed around them, let them part in front of me and seal behind. i thought i’d move past them, but they always got there first.

Exported image of a generative software art piece by LIA, www.liaworks.com, 2022. Still: 3840 px × 2160 px (4k). Edition of 1 + 1 AP (not minted).
